<p>Back to the <a href="grammar.eng.html">grammar's main page</a>. </p>

<p>The section <a href="alphabet.eng.html">Alphabet</a> presents a list of all Skolt Sámi letters.
Here the pronunciation of Skolt Sámi <em>vowel letters</em> is explained using comparison to English
and in some cases to other languages. </p>

<p>On the site <a href="../exercise/exercise.eng.html">Pronunciation exercise</a> you can practice
to distinguish between the different letters by listening and writing. </p>

<p>The chart below shows Skolt Sámi example words. In the three columns on the right side you can
click on links and listen how these words are pronounced in the three different dialects <em
class="lg_mat">Peäc'cam</em> 'Petsamo/Pechenga' (which corresponds to the pronunciation of most
Skolt Sámi from Nellim today and which is also closest to the old Neiden-dialect), <em
class="lg_mat">Suõˊnn'jel</em> 'Suonikylä' (which corresponds to the pronunciation of most Skolt
Sámi from Sevettijärvi today) or <em class="lg_mat">Njuõˊttjäuˊrr</em> 'Notozero' (which corresponds
to the pronunciation of most Skolt Sámi from Russia today). </p>

<p>Remember that all vowels can be long or short. Long vowels are written double. </p>

